org.gradoop.flink.algorithms.gelly.randomjump.functions

Class VCIComputeFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.graph.pregel.ComputeFunction<Long,VCIVertexValue,Long,org.apache.flink.types.NullValue>
      • org.gradoop.flink.algorithms.gelly.randomjump.functions.VCIComputeFunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class VCIComputeFunction
extends org.apache.flink.graph.pregel.ComputeFunction<Long,VCIVertexValue,Long,org.apache.flink.types.NullValue>
    Compute function for KRandomJumpGellyVCI. Vertex values are of type VCIVertexValue, with fields:
    • f0: Boolean set to true if the vertex was visited, to false otherwise
    • f1: List<Long> containing all long indices from already visited outgoing edges
    A message of type NullValue from one vertex to another is a walk respective a jump to this other vertex and therefor considered as one of k walkers.

                    org.apache.flink.graph.pregel.MessageIterator<org.apache.flink.types.NullValue> messages)
        Initially starts the first walk or jump from the given start vertices. Afterwards starts a walk or jump from a vertex, if it received messages from other vertices. Stops the computation and therefor the iteration if the number of currently visited vertices exceeds the number of vertices to visit.
